  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0 \u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 : \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd : \u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Prime Minister Ranil's house set on fire : Chandrika condemns : International expresses concern",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe's private residence was attacked and set on fire during a demonstration in Colombo on Saturday 09th, demanding the resignation of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa and his government.",
        "Former President Chandrika Bandaranaike Kumaratunga has condemned this and Norway and Afghanistan have expressed concern.",
        "On 09th, some of the protestors protested at Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe's private residence complex located on 5th Street, Colombo. After some time they started attacking the house as well.",
        "As a result, the police and the armed forces were engaged in security duties at the Prime Minister's residence. Tear gas was also used to disperse the protesters. However, the demonstrators did not leave.",
        "Following this, news broke that the Prime Minister's residence had been set on fire and video footage of the fire was shared on social media. During this, it is reported that the library set up in the Prime Minister's private residence has caught fire.",
        "Various parties have expressed their condemnation for setting fire to the Prime Minister's residence. The reason is because the prime minister has decided to give the said house to Colombo Royal College.",
        "Lawyer NK Ashokbaran has posted on his Twitter site, 'Ranil Wickramasinghe has given his house to a government school after him.",
        "Apart from that, we have seen in his interview videos that there is a library with valuable books inside that house. \"Setting fire to such a house is a heinous crime,\" he said.",
        "Former President Chandrika Bandaranaike Kumaratunga tweeted, 'I strongly condemn the burning of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe's house.",
        "Protesters do not need violence to achieve their goal of ousting a bad government and establishing people's rule.' mentioned that.",
        "J.V.P. said that 'not to engage in violent activities such as arson, looting, etc., which will set back the victory achieved in the moral struggle'. President Anurakumara Dissanayake mentioned.",
        "The international community has also expressed concern over the burning of the Prime Minister's residence. The Norwegian ambassador to Sri Lanka said in his Twitter post, 'It is worrying that the peaceful protests have turned violent and the Prime Minister's house has been burnt.",
        "Violence cannot be justified under any circumstances. We call upon all parties concerned to prevent the escalation of violence. Protesters should not take the law into their own hands.' mentioned that.",
        "'Violence, destruction of public and private property is unjustified. Such violation of public order in Sri Lanka deepens the country's problems. It affects many countries around the world. It is noteworthy that the Afghan ambassador posted on Twitter that solutions can only be found through national unity and international assistance."
      ],
